  intro: `This course treats Atlanta as a living exhibit — a city written and rewritten through its music, its image, its news. Students in ENGRD 328W investigated how gender and race are represented, and mis-represented, across Atlanta's media ecosystems: the hip-hop studios of the Southside, the soundstages rebranding the city as the New Hollywood, the newsrooms that cover Buford Highway but rarely from it. What follows is their archive: essays, photographs, and citations gathered over one semester of looking closely.`,

